name: Starcrossed
description: Some loves are ended too soon, others are never meant to be. But can the temporal anomaly crisis change that? Or is it merely threatening to tear existing relationships apart?
rules:
-- In this Hybrid Event, you will complete Supply Missions in one Phase, and Ship Battles in another Phase.
-- There are two Phases to this Event! Each Phase is individually timed.
-- Unique Ship Battles and Supply Missions are available during the event. Open the Event to access them.
-- Using any version of Dax, Chakotay, Tyler, Romantic crew or crew with a matching battle trait will provide a bonus to Ship Battles and Supply Missions.
-- Using the U.S.S. Yang, the U.S.S. Yeager, or the Nova Class ship will provide a hull bonus in Skirmish Battles.
-- Community Rewards are also available during Phase 1 only. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock these rewards before the phase change!
-- Every Ship Battle or Supply Mission you complete earns you Event Victory Points. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock Threshold Rewards!
-- In this event, Squadrons may also compete to advance up the Squadron leaderboards. Join a Squadron to get more rewards!
bonus_text: Crew Bonus: Dax, Chakotay, Tyler, or Romantic
rewards_teaser: Reach Rank 1 by gaining Victory Points from Event Missions!

featured_crew.flavor: Infected with an incurable disease, Chakotay and Janeway are placed on an unknown planet while a cure is sought.

screens.text: "I'm not one to complain, but it's getting harder and harder to avoid breaking the reassociation taboo when there are several versions of other symbionts and their hosts in the present."
"I may not be a joined Trill, but I absolutely get having to relive all of my past romantic mistakes. It's not exactly pleasant."
"That's because you're looking at it from the wrong angle. This is an opportunity to fix past mistakes and explore what might have been."
"Explore whatever possibilities you want. But there's a reason why we have a taboo against rehashing the past."
"I'm not one to complain, but it's getting harder and harder to avoid breaking the reassociation taboo when there are several versions of other symbionts and their hosts in the present."
"I may not be a joined Trill, but I absolutely get having to relive all of my past romantic mistakes. It's not exactly pleasant."
"That's because you're looking at it from the wrong angle. This is an opportunity to fix past mistakes and explore what might have been."
"Explore whatever possibilities you want. But there's a reason why we have a taboo against rehashing the past."

"Nice work, Captain. I think you helped set some good parameters to keep things civil while we continue to deal with the anomaly crisis. Unfortunately, not everyone has been as receptive. Our impatient friend took it upon himself to make off with a ship from spacedock."

responses.text: "Being a little lovestruck is one thing; stealing a Starfleet vessel is another."
"I think she's moved on. You might be in for some heartbreak."

screens.text: "I'm going to find Michael. I'm not going to allow this opportunity to slip away. I believe we're here in the same time for a reason."

"And yet it seems to happen a lot around here, doesn't it? Have some confidence in me, Captain. The Yang has access to Michael's movements - specifically the Michael from my timeline - and that's the one I need to see."
"Even if she has, I need to hear it from her. I need to see her. One last time.  To make sense of a few things. For closure."
"What binds her and I now is none of your concern. This is different. This may be my last chance to reunite with Michael - or at least get closure. And I need to take it."

"If he hasn't been able to reach her through normal channels, that's a pretty good sign she doesn't want to be reached. Either way, we need to take back the USS Yang - and maybe spare Tyler's dignity and his heart in the process."
